This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as object classification, semantic segmentation, and object detection, which are typically associated with the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses language modeling, which falls under the cs.CL sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks for these tasks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Finally, the emphasis on power efficiency and the use of dilated separable convolutions may make this paper relevant to the cs.NE sub-category.
